WEBVTT



00:00:00.608 --> 00:00:02.144
Good morning everyone

00:00:02.208 --> 00:00:03.936
My name's Tandy.

00:00:03.968 --> 00:00:08.256
Today I'll be talking to you about finding hope in a fragile world.

00:00:08.032 --> 00:00:11.008
and what the hope of Christmas really means to me.

00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:15.488
From a young age my parents have always been insistent

00:00:15.424 --> 00:00:20.192
On Christmas being a time that we pray together before opening gifts.

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:23.488
It's always been a time that our family comes together.

00:00:23.392 --> 00:00:24.640
To eat

00:00:24.384 --> 00:00:27.296
And celebrate and often partake in communion.

00:00:28.512 --> 00:00:31.104
Kushner's always been a busy time for me.

00:00:31.584 --> 00:00:34.720
I remember many things that the church has organised.

00:00:34.528 --> 00:00:36.288
Like Christmas at the park.

00:00:36.256 --> 00:00:39.328
Where we unite people from all walks of the life.

00:00:39.552 --> 00:00:41.696
And the christingle service.

00:00:41.504 --> 00:00:43.808
Connecting the four corners of the world

00:00:43.616 --> 00:00:45.824
Inspiring the light of Jesus.

00:00:46.304 --> 00:00:49.056
I remember Carole singing at a nursing home.

00:00:49.120 --> 00:00:51.744
And seeing a woman crying tears of joy.

00:00:52.928 --> 00:00:55.136
I remember donating to charity.

00:00:54.880 --> 00:00:56.672
And the shoebox appeal.

00:00:57.824 --> 00:01:02.560
And when we see the video and the joy that you see on the young children's faces.

00:01:02.624 --> 00:01:03.424
Thank you.

00:01:03.424 --> 00:01:08.128
I remember feeling proud every time I was picked in the right nativities at school.

00:01:09.248 --> 00:01:13.632
I've certainly always found comfort and excitement in Christmas.

00:01:14.144 --> 00:01:19.520
I even remember receiving oatmeal to sprinkle on the ground for Santa's reindeer to eat.

00:01:20.960 --> 00:01:22.432
As i've grown

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:24.064
I've come to realize

00:01:23.872 --> 00:01:27.776
Where the spirit of giving at Christmas really comes from.

00:01:28.992 --> 00:01:34.176
And that spirit of giving comes from the gift of Jesus that God blessed us with.

00:01:34.528 --> 00:01:37.088
He is the present that brings love.

00:01:36.992 --> 00:01:38.048
Hope.

00:01:37.888 --> 00:01:39.648
Joy and peace.

00:01:40.736 --> 00:01:42.560
He's the promised Messiah.

00:01:42.848 --> 00:01:45.760
And I think that's the true significance of giving.

00:01:46.208 --> 00:01:49.248
It symbolizes the gift of Jesus.

00:01:49.280 --> 00:01:50.752
For all of us.

00:01:51.328 --> 00:01:53.600
And we're demonstrating the peace

00:01:53.312 --> 00:01:54.464
Love

00:01:54.208 --> 00:01:57.088
Joy and hope Jesus brought to us.

00:01:57.696 --> 00:02:02.816
I'd like to invite Mandy to come and read Isaiah 9:6-7 for me.

00:02:12.768 --> 00:02:22.528
This will happen when this special child is born. God will give us a son who will be responsible for leading the people.

00:02:22.848 --> 00:02:25.408
His name will be wonderful

00:02:25.184 --> 00:02:26.912
Counselor

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:31.968
Powerful God, Father, who lives forever, Prince of Peace.

00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:36.032
His power will continue to grow

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:37.888
and there will be

00:02:37.888 --> 00:02:40.096
Peace without end

00:02:40.192 --> 00:02:48.192
This will establish him as the king sitting on David's throne and ruining his kingdom.

00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:50.912
Good job, Randy.

00:02:56.832 --> 00:02:59.584
And so when we're celebrating at Christmas,

00:02:59.328 --> 00:03:04.448
I think one thing we're really celebrating is the fulfillment of God's promises.

00:03:05.664 --> 00:03:09.792
We often talk about hope without fully considering the significance of it.

00:03:09.792 --> 00:03:16.640
And I think hope can be defined as having unwavering trust in the unchanging character of God.

00:03:16.832 --> 00:03:21.856
Hope anchors us and strengthens us. It turns our focus to God.

00:03:21.600 --> 00:03:24.960
Rather than whatever difficult circumstance we may be in.

00:03:25.920 --> 00:03:28.096
Even in her circumstances

00:03:27.968 --> 00:03:29.600
Mary had hope.

00:03:29.408 --> 00:03:31.104
and trust in God.

00:03:31.264 --> 00:03:34.496
When she was told to conceive the promised Messiah.

00:03:35.360 --> 00:03:38.112
Romans 12:12 says

00:03:37.952 --> 00:03:39.840
Rejoice in hope.

00:03:39.712 --> 00:03:42.048
Be patient in tribulation.

00:03:41.824 --> 00:03:44.000
And be constant in prayer

00:03:46.368 --> 00:03:51.328
So if we come back to the topic of finding hope in this fragile world

00:03:53.088 --> 00:03:57.248
I hope that through this short message I've been able to communicate with you.

00:03:56.992 --> 00:04:00.064
the great hope you can have in Jesus Christ.

00:04:00.256 --> 00:04:04.480
I want to speak to anyone in this room who is feeling a sense of fear in this time.

00:04:04.512 --> 00:04:07.744
To anyone who's feeling anxious about any situation

00:04:07.936 --> 00:04:14.144
To anyone who may be Christmas isn't a time of joy or it may bring back some sad events.

00:04:15.648 --> 00:04:18.176
God provides for the beds of the earth.

00:04:18.272 --> 00:04:20.832
So how much more will he provide for you?

00:04:21.952 --> 00:04:25.504
He gives us assurance in 2 Timothy 1:7.

00:04:25.312 --> 00:04:28.960
Which says for god has not given us the spirit of fear

00:04:28.736 --> 00:04:32.416
But that of power and of love and of a sound mind.

00:04:32.352 --> 00:04:37.632
And so we have been told by Paul in his book to the Philippians 4:6,

00:04:38.016 --> 00:04:40.000
To be anxious for nothing

00:04:39.904 --> 00:04:46.656
But in every situation, by prayer and petition, with thanksgiving, present your request to God.

00:04:48.768 --> 00:04:52.320
There are three things I want everyone to take away from this.

00:04:52.096 --> 00:04:58.368
The first is to have hope, have unwavering trust in his unchanging character.

00:04:58.400 --> 00:05:03.072
In every situation, be still and know that he is in charge.

00:05:03.584 --> 00:05:04.960
Secondly,

00:05:05.056 --> 00:05:07.456
Be certain in his plan

00:05:07.840 --> 00:05:15.872
He knows the plans he has for all of you and their plans to prosper you and not harm you and to give you a great hope and a good future.

00:05:17.440 --> 00:05:23.264
I want to encourage you all to go out into the world and spread the good news of the gospel.

00:05:23.456 --> 00:05:25.600
Spread the love joy

00:05:25.408 --> 00:05:27.936
Peace and hope of Jesus.

00:05:29.088 --> 00:05:31.392
I just want to leave with all of us.

00:05:31.552 --> 00:05:32.768
The prefer

00:05:33.088 --> 00:05:36.928
That he would make us all a channel of his peace.

00:05:37.216 --> 00:05:43.872
Where there's despair in this world that we would bring hope to other people and we would love with all of our souls.

00:05:45.856 --> 00:05:49.728
I pray that the peace of God surpasses all understanding.

00:05:49.536 --> 00:05:51.904
Would rule your hearts this Christmas.

00:05:51.712 --> 00:05:53.184
In Jesus' name.

00:06:03.136 --> 00:06:04.768
Thank you, Tony.

00:06:04.960 --> 00:06:06.176
What a treat
